“I understood everything while studying, but I just can’t seem to remember anything” is a complaint that most students struggle with. As students, we are expected not just to understand but also to remember information. Spending hours studying before an exam but not being able to recall specific details in the examination hall can be pretty frustrating. The solution to this problem is to employ study techniques that help you retain information better. On that note, a few study techniques that you can implement to boost your memory are:
                            <br>
                            1. Use Mnemonics 
                            <br>
                            2. Create a Memory Palace 
                            <br>
                            3. Explain the Information in Your Own Words 
                            <br>
                            4. Take Brief Notes 
                            <br>
                            5. Create Flashcards 
                            <br>
